║   MODEL A: POPULATION OFFSET (Constant Per-Capita Rates)    ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

SPECIFICATION:
  Background: μ(d,y) = population × exp(β₀ + Σ β_year)
  Triggering: α(marks) = exp(β₀_trig + β_violence·violent + β_state·intervention)
  Kernel: g(t) = exp(-β·t)
  Intensity: λ(t) = μ(d,y) + Σ α(marks_i)·g(t-t_i)

KEY ASSUMPTION:
  → Districts with 2× population have 2× the protest rate
  → Per-capita rates are constant across population sizes
  → Population is an EXPOSURE term, not a predictor

PARAMETERS (14 total):
  Background (10): β₀, β_2016...β_2024 (NO γ parameter)
  Triggering (3): β₀_trig, β_violence, β_state
  Decay (1): β

